{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17606340","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17606340"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T13:11:45+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T13:11:45+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15915"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15915","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15915"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8606"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72389"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8606","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8606"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15915"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57859"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4949"},{"type":"tags","id":"5586"},{"type":"tags","id":"7493"},{"type":"tags","id":"8730"},{"type":"tags","id":"8731"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20613"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20620"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72389","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/72389"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EDuring week four of embryological development, thickened regions of surface ectoderm called otic placodes appear adjacent to the developing hindbrain. These placodes invaginate to form otic pits that subsequently close to form otic vesicles.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following structures develops directly from the otic vesicle?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Membranous labyrinth","Ossicles of the middle ear","Tympanic membrane","Eustachian tube","External auditory meatus"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Emembranous labyrinth\u003C/strong\u003E develops directly from the otic vesicle. The otic vesicle undergoes complex folding to form the various components of the membranous labyrinth including the semicircular ducts, utricle, saccule, and cochlear duct.\u003C/p\u003E    \u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options develop from other embryological structures:\u003C/p\u003E    \u003Cul\u003E        \u003Cli\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eossicles\u003C/strong\u003E develop from the first and second pharyngeal arches\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Etympanic membrane\u003C/strong\u003E forms where the first pharyngeal cleft meets the first pharyngeal pouch\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003EEustachian tube\u003C/strong\u003E develops from the first pharyngeal pouch\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eexternal auditory meatus\u003C/strong\u003E develops from the first pharyngeal cleft\u003C/li\u003E    \u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The otic vesicle develops from the otic placode at week four of embryological development.","The otic vesicle gives rise to the membranous labyrinth of the inner ear.","The cochlear duct develops from the ventral portion of the otic vesicle."],"references":["Sadler TW. Langman\u0027s Medical Embryology: Wolters Kluwer; 2015.","Helwany M, Arbor TC, Tadi P. Embryology, Ear. [Updated 2023 Aug 8]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/books/NBK557588/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57859"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15915"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57859","links":{"self":"https://app.emedi